<p>So what is it? Let me introduce you because of course, there&rsquo;s far too much to cover in one post. I would like to get into the more advanced stuff ideally. One of the things that annoys me is that there are a ton of <em>&ldquo;Getting Started with the Basics&rdquo;</em> types posts and videos and not enough that go deeper into the features. It feels like I&rsquo;ve absorbed a lot of the content that&rsquo;s out there, however..it only feels right to start with the basics and then build on top of that.</p>
<h2 id="org-is-a-language">Org is a language</h2>
<p><a href="https://orgmode.org/">Org-mode</a> can do a lot of cool things. At it&rsquo;s core Org is a plain text, Markdown type language. It has a slightly different but familiiar syntax to <a href="https://www.markdownguide.org/getting-started/">Markdown</a> that straps on a ton of very useful features for organization and productivity. I&rsquo;ve seen it referred to as &lsquo;Org-down&rsquo;. Many will be familiar with the idea of plain text, most of our text entry to the internet or through are phones is usually in plain text with no special formatting . Most will also be aware of the Rich Text Format (.rft). You may have come across this is in your text editor of choice, writing an email, and certain other places where you have to write posts with more formatting. We might have options in a toolbar for Bold, Italics, Headings, Colours, Alignment etc. Markdown (.md) is a form of plain text with symbols that can be used to enhance the formatting when we publish text.</p>
<p>For example in Markdown..</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" style="background-color:#f0f0f0;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"><code class="language-markdown" data-lang="markdown"><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">1</span><span><span style="color:#000080;font-weight:bold"># This is a level 1 heading
</span></span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">2</span><span><span style="color:#000080;font-weight:bold"></span>
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">3</span><span><span style="color:#800080;font-weight:bold">## This is a second level heading
</span></span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">4</span><span><span style="color:#800080;font-weight:bold"></span>
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">5</span><span><span style="font-style:italic">*Bold*</span>
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">6</span><span><span style="font-style:italic">_Italics_</span>
</span></span></code></pre></div><p>and in Org..</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" style="background-color:#f0f0f0;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"><code class="language-org" data-lang="org"><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">1</span><span><span style="color:#000080;font-weight:bold">*</span><span style="font-weight:bold"> This is a level 1 heading</span>
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">2</span><span>
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">3</span><span><span style="color:#800080;font-weight:bold">**</span> This is a second level heading
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">4</span><span>
